     This function registers a callback for a spaceball to report buttons.  A
     spaceball has six axes of freedom (three of motion and three of orienta-
     tion), plus buttons.  The spaceball has glutDeviceGet(  [1mGLUT_NUM_SPACE-[0m
     [1mBALL_BUTTONS)  [22mand numbers them from 1.  Button state is either  [1mGLUT_UP[0m
     or  [1mGLUT_DOWN.[0m

     The callback is bound to the  current window  .

[1mCAVEATS[0m
     OpenGLUT does not implement spaceball support.

     In contrast, mouse buttons are numbered from 0 in the GLUT API.  This is
     a wrinkle.

